      • moveBalanced

        protected static Move moveBalanced​(Entity main,
                                   Entity moveTo)
        Calculates where the main should move to get closer to moveTo. However, 'balanced' means, that if the yDistance is greater than xDistance, it will chose to move in y instead of x.
        Parameters:
        main - The entity of our perspective.
        moveTo - The entity we're moving towards.
        Returns:
        A move that should decrease the distance between the two.

      • smallestDistance

        protected static Entity smallestDistance​(Entity main,
                                         java.util.List<? extends Entity> entities)
        Returns the entity that has the smallest distance to main entity. If the main entity is in the given list, ignores it. If there are no entities other than main in this list, returns null.
        Parameters:
        main - Main entity those distance to other entities is being compared to.
        entities - List of entities that will have their distance to entity checked.
        Returns:
        Closest entity in taxicab distance to main or null if none found.
